parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the motorcycle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the rider stranded.
symptoms: The motorcycle stalls or dies while in operation
the check engine light comes on
the throttle is unresponsive
the motorcycle has no power
the battery cover falls open while riding.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery cover can cause a distraction while riding, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the rider stranded.
symptoms: The battery cover falls open while riding
the cover hits the rider's leg
the electrical components are exposed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signals can cause confusion or miscommunication with other drivers, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The turn signals fail to flash after applying the service brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank cap can cause fuel to leak or spray out of the tank, creating a fire hazard, and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel leaks or sprays out of the fuel tank cap when the tank is approximately half full or when the bike is tipped on its side
fuel gauge malfunctions
fuel gauge readings change erratically
fuel leaks onto the engine and rider.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the clutch lever can cause difficulty in operating the clutch, leading to loss of control, accidents, or falls.
symptoms: The clutch lever feels far to reach
sticks or ratchets
and is not smooth to operate
making it hard to control the vehicle in slow operation and turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the compensator sprocket assembly can cause catastrophic failure, leading to operator injury or death.
symptoms: An audible loud knock is heard coming from the primary chain case on each engine startup
originating from the compensator sprocket assembly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear sprocket bolts can cause the rear wheel to lock up, leading to accidents or crashes.
symptoms: The bolts that hold the rear sprocket to the wheel back out
causing a potential catastrophic failure.
